about.summary: Analysis and visualization toolkit for volumetric data

name: yt
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "3.6.0" %}

package:
  name: yt
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/y/yt/yt-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: effb00536f19fd2bdc18f67dacd5550b82066a6adce5b928f27a01d7505109ec

build:
  number: 2
  entry_points:
    - yt = yt.utilities.command_line:run_main
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - numpy
    - cython >=0.24.0
  run:
    - python
    - ipython >=1.0
    # _png was removed around version 3 and that broke yt.
    - matplotlib-base >=1.5.3,<3
    - numpy >=1.10.4
    - setuptools >=19.6
    - sympy >=1.0
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  imports:
    - yt
  commands:
    - pip check
    - yt --help
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: http://yt-project.org/
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: COPYING.txt
  summary: Analysis and visualization toolkit for volumetric data

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ngoldbaum
    - munkm
